{
  "message": "fuzz(alloc-succinct): 19 structured seeds across rank/select/find shapes\n\nExisting 10 seeds left several boundary classes uncovered. Add 19\nseeds spanning the SuccinctBitmap operation matrix:\n\n  bitmap shapes:\n    * empty (0 bytes)\n    * single byte: all-zero, all-one, 0xAA / 0x55 alternating\n    * 8 / 16 / 32 / 64 / 128 / 256 / 512 byte sizes\n    * sparse single-bit-at-100, single-zero-hole-at-515\n    * checkerboard 0x33, 0xF0 nibble pattern\n    * leading 16-byte 0xFF run + 48-byte zero tail (long-run find)\n    * two short isolated one-runs (find_contiguous probe stress)\n\n  rank/select/find probe vectors:\n    * boundary positions (0, len-1, len, len+1, len+64)\n    * trailing-mask boundary (len=50 over a fully-set 8-byte block)\n    * select past population (k > model_ones returns None)\n    * find_contiguous run_len = 0 / 1 / len / len+1 / len*2 / 4097\n    * full-density rank/select/find probe arrays (16 each)\n\n26K runs / 11s post-seed surface no crashes.",
